{
  "stem": "1415.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And some of them wore hats, those-- those German hats-- those lovely-- their-- their-- their regalia, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And how they treated the women.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "I remember watching, that there was some kind of a counter there in the middle when we went through after we were separated.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And I guess, I don't know, we were changed and-- and-- and dressed, how-- how-- I remember this one German.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And this woman was naked naturally-- how he made her bend over that counter, whatever it was, and took the poke and poked her in her butt and had somebody look into her butt to see whether she had some jewelry inside her rectum.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] And how they went around and looked at everybody.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And some of us were shaved, some of us were not.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "It was-- I guess in the life of Auschwitz, it was already at the end of it-- towards the end of it, even though I-- I didn't [? omit ?] the most horrifying killing took place after I came there.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "The burning and the gassing took-- was night and day after we got there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "But still, if you measure it in months, it was towards the end of Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember after they-- after they went through us real thoroughly, I-- I felt like I was just an observer there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "I was sitting and observing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "I was-- it didn't involve me at all.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "I wasn't part of it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "I-- I managed to get myself out of that-- of that place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "I wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And we-- they took us out on the platform, naked, and we stood there for 24 hours, naked on the platform.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "Evidently, what might have happened, they had no specified place for us.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
